# Terraform Conventions

## Module Structure

Every module must have these files:
```
module-name/
├── main.tf          # Resources
├── variables.tf     # Input variables
├── outputs.tf       # Output values
└── versions.tf      # Required providers and version constraints
```

## `for_each` over `count`

```hcl
# CORRECT — named map, survives reordering
resource "github_repository" "repos" {
  for_each = { for repo in var.repos : repo.name => repo }

  name        = each.value.name
  description = each.value.description
  visibility  = each.value.visibility
}

# WRONG — count breaks when list changes order
resource "github_repository" "repos" {
  count = length(var.repos)
  name  = var.repos[count.index].name
}
```

Use `count` ONLY for boolean toggles (enable/disable a single resource).

## Tagging (all AWS resources)

```hcl
locals {
  common_tags = {
    Workspace   = "iron-layer-dev-workspace"
    ManagedBy   = "terraform"
    Product     = var.product_name   # "ironlayer" | "foundation" | "autopilot"
    Client      = var.client_id
    Environment = var.environment
  }
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket" "example" {
  bucket = "${var.client_id}-${var.environment}-raw"
  tags   = local.common_tags
}
```

## S3 Backend with DynamoDB Locking

```hcl
# versions.tf
terraform {
  required_version = ">= 1.9"

  backend "s3" {
    bucket         = "exodus-terraform-state"
    key            = "${var.client_id}/${var.environment}/${module.name}.tfstate"
    region         = "us-east-1"
    dynamodb_table = "exodus-terraform-state-lock"
    encrypt        = true
  }

  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 5.0"
    }
    databricks = {
      source  = "databricks/databricks"
      version = "~> 1.0"
    }
    github = {
      source  = "integrations/github"
      version = "~> 6.0"
    }
  }
}
```

## Security Baselines

- Never add `0.0.0.0/0` ingress to security groups
- Always enable KMS key rotation (`enable_key_rotation = true`)
- Enable S3 versioning and server-side encryption on all buckets
- IAM: least-privilege policies, no wildcard actions on sensitive resources
- Databricks: Unity Catalog grants at catalog/schema/table level, not wildcard

## exodus-terraform: GitHub Org Management

```hcl
# github/repos.tf — all ironlayer org repos managed here
module "ironlayer_oss" {
  source = "./modules/github_repo"

  name        = "ironlayer_oss"
  description = "IronLayer — SQL control plane for data engineers"
  visibility  = "public"
  topics      = ["databricks", "dbt", "data-engineering", "sql", "mcp"]

  branch_protection = {
    required_reviews = 1
    require_status_checks = ["ci", "lint", "test"]
    allow_force_pushes = false
  }

  environments = ["staging", "production"]
  secrets      = ["ANTHROPIC_API_KEY", "DATABRICKS_TOKEN"]
}
```

## State Management

```
exodus-terraform state key:   ironlayer-org/{resource}.tfstate
ironlayer_infra state key:    {client_id}/{environment}/{module}.tfstate
```

Never run `terraform apply` locally on production environments without:
1. `terraform plan` output reviewed by a human
2. CI passing (lint + validate + plan)
3. Approval via GitHub PR

## Formatting and Validation (CI checks)

```bash
terraform fmt -check -recursive .   # fail if not formatted
terraform validate                   # validate configuration
tfsec .                              # security scan
```

Always run `terraform fmt` before committing.
